index.html.keywords: About TAML - Tab Annotated Markup Language Defining the coolest and simplest markup language delimited ONLY by tabs and carriage returns All TAML documents adhere to these rules STRICTLY New entries are separated by carriage returns (CR / CRLF) Keys and values are separated by 1+ tab characters (\t) Subkeys are defined on a line starting with 1+ tab characters (\t) An array is a key with multiple child values Presence of space characters are illegal Comments TBD See the Articles to Get Started.
